						<div class="postbody">Well if it's only flickering, that's not the worst thing in the world. Actually, I kind of like the way sprite flickering looks; it characterizes NES games. I believe it was kyuusaku who was saying the same thing about attribute glitches, and I can see where he's coming from with that. If it doesn't cause RAM corruption where random values are just littered all over the sprite page, I guess it's alright. I was really worried because in my polygon sequence engine, I use a sprite zero hit to shut the screen off 40 scanlines early, spilling 40 scanlines out of Vblank, and I have sprites on screen with this engine. So this seems like a perfect candidate for the corruption.
<br />
<br />There's probably tons we still don't know about the PPU. I can't imagine trying to find this bug though; I wouldn't have the slightest clue where to begin. Yes, thanks blargg for going through tedious crap to find yet another weird quirk with the NES <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />.</div>

					
